<h id='hoverNowWorksHierarchical'><a href="https://w3future.com/weblog/2002/05/11.xml#a99" class="weblogItemTitle">:hover now works hierarchical</a></h>
<blockquote cite='http://markpasc.org/blog/2002/05/10.html#i33037PM'><p>The annoying part for me is he proceeds to demonstrate using display:blocked anchors for box-shaped links and how easily a :hover style is applied, when my sidebar boxes (at least on the main page) have :hover styles that (again, at least in K-Meleon 0.6) only work if you don't mouse over the content in the boxes, just the boxes. Gah. [<a href='http://markpasc.org/blog/'>markpasc.blog</a>]</p></blockquote>
<p>Then I think you'd like to know <a href="http://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=5693">this bug has just been fixed</a> in <a href="http://www.mozilla.org/releases/#1.0rc2">Mozilla RC2.</a></p>
